de.learnlib.api.algorithm.feature

Interface ResumableLearner<T extends Serializable>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the serializable learner state.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAutomatonLStar, AbstractDTLearner, AbstractExtensibleAutomatonLStar, AbstractTTTLearner, ADTLearner, ClassicLStarDFA, ClassicLStarMealy, DTLearnerDFA, DTLearnerMealy, ExtensibleLStarDFA, ExtensibleLStarMealy, KearnsVaziraniDFA, KearnsVaziraniMealy, MalerPnueliDFA, MalerPnueliMealy, MealyDHC, PrefixTTTLearnerDFA, RivestSchapireDFA, RivestSchapireMealy, TTTLearnerDFA, TTTLearnerMealy

    public interface ResumableLearner<T extends Serializable>
    Learning algorithms that implement this interface can be "suspended" by means of exposing a serializable state object that contains all data that is necessary to resume learning process from a previous state.
    Author:
    bainczyk

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void resume(T state)
      Does not get the learner to continue learning.
      T suspend()
      Expose the serializable learner state object.

    • Method Detail

      • suspend

        T suspend()
        Expose the serializable learner state object.

        Does not stop a running learning process. Since most data structures that are used during learning are mutable, use this method inside of a learning loop with care.

        Returns:
        The learner state.

      • resume

        void resume(T state)
        Does not get the learner to continue learning. Instead, the learner updates its internal state according to the given state object.
        Parameters:
        state - The learner state.
